Derivatio nominis.
The new species is named after the talented Sicilian doctor, botanist and naturalist Francesco Minà Palumbo (Castelbuono, 
14 March 1814
– 
12 March 1899
) (

), who dedicated his entire life to the study of nature, especially on the Madonie Mts., where he lived from birth to death (

).
